pullRequest.body:
- replace `isOpen_uniformity` with `nhds_eq_comap_uniformity`
  as I suggested in #2028
- don't extend `UniformSpace.Core` so that we can drop `refl`,
  as it follows from `nhds_eq_comap_uniformity`;
- drop `UniformSpace.mk'` - can't be a `match_pattern` anymore;
- deprecate `UniformSpace.ofNhdsEqComap`.
---

This docstring looks useless to me if one doesn't already know what this is about, could you expand it a little bit?

```suggestion
/-- Build a `UniformSpace` from a `UniformSpace.Core` and a compatible topology.
Use `UnifiormSpace.mk` instead to avoid proving
the unnecessary assumption `UniformSpace.Core.refl`.

The main constructor used to use a different compatibility assumption.
This definition was created as a step towards porting to a new definition.
Now the main definition is ported,
so this constructor will be removed in a few months. -/
```
